\section{Introduction}

% TODO: introduction

The technology behind chatbots \cite{Gong2008,bradesko2012} has become an usual element in our everyday life, having played an important role in the development of many fields, including education and online tutoring \cite{clarizia2018,Smutny2020}. These automatic systems ease personalized learning, adapting individuals' pace of learning, who get personalized online tutoring outside the classroom.

A chatbot is a program that allows the machine to communicate in a similar way as a human does \cite{Gong2008}. Chatbots can significantly contribute to providing interactive learning experience as well as individual attention \cite{agarwal2020}.

In this sense, chatbot technology offers a great opportunity for the improvement of tutoring systems \cite{Daniel2016,agarwal2020}, as not all students are comfortable with face-to-face tutoring with the instructor. In fact, in many cases, students suffer stress when they have to ask a question in front of the entire class. This is why many students prefer to remain silent and ask their question later via email. 
However, this means a waste of time and a delay of hours or even days to get the teacher's answer.
Chatbot technology has a potential to fill the gap between teacher and students, helping them to solve questions and carry out a dynamic and autonomous learning \cite{Griol2014,kim2020}.
Moreover, using an automated system such as a chatbot allows the teacher to detect those topics that are most in demand, and on which he or she should consequently place more emphasis in class.


